Texts, role-play, exercises, listening- and video materials. Mini student presentations and active participation in group work and active learning.

Assessment methods - there is a language test after every mini-bloc.  There are four mini-tests. Students will present 3 mini-reports sharing knowledge on Sweden. If the student passes all the tests and meets all the requirements the pass/fail exam will be granted in the end of the term. In case of web-based learning, there will be a final online test.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to acquire basic conversational-level Swedish, that is the grammar, pronunciation and intonation as well as basic vocabulary and a range of phrases necessary for communicating different needs. There is also some background information about Sweden, its regions, history, traditions and way of life.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the students are able to understand simple Swedish and speak about the topics covered in the programme. They are able to read with the help of the dictionary and write simple sentences.
